- PATCH acceptable: false

- The editCoverItem method handles HTTP requests to /printshops/{id}/pricetable/covers and is specifically mapped to PUT requests. That means this operation supports only PUT; other HTTP methods are not implemented for this endpoint in the provided code.
- There is a separate method (addNewCoverItem) on the same path using POST, but it serves a different operation (adding new items). It does not change the fact that editCoverItem itself only accepts PUT.
- The absence of explicit mappings for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, DELETE, and PATCH means those methods are not supported by this endpoint according to the code.
